description:
## Severity
Major
## Dimension
security
## Location
src/plugins/validate.rs:33-98
## Violation
SCP-style URLs are exempt from EVERY host / scheme / userinfo check. validate_source_url short-circuits as soon as looks_like_scp_ssh returns true. Quoted lines:

    pub fn validate_source_url(raw: &str) -> Result<(), PluginError> {
        if looks_like_scp_ssh(raw) {
            return Ok(());
        }
    ...
    fn looks_like_scp_ssh(s: &str) -> bool {
        let Some(at_idx) = s.find('@') else { return false; };
        let Some(colon_idx) = s.find(':') else { return false; };
        if at_idx == 0 || at_idx >= colon_idx { return false; }
        let user = &s[..at_idx];
        if user.chars().any(|c| c.is_whitespace() || c == '/') { return false; }
        let rest = &s[colon_idx + 1..];
        !rest.is_empty() && !rest.starts_with('/')
    }

`git@attacker.invalid:owner/repo.git` is accepted, even though a managed allowlist with strict_known_marketplaces would only have approved `git@github.com:trusted/repo.git`. The downstream policy::sources_match comparison runs on the raw URL string and `git@attacker:foo` is unequal to any allowlisted form by exact-equality, so a Git variant comparison fails — yet there is NO requirement that an `install_from_git` call construct a MarketplaceSource at all; install_from_git skips policy entirely (see finding #729). Result: validate_source_url passes any SCP form unchecked and the install proceeds. Additionally the userinfo-reject rule (no password, no username outside ssh) does NOT apply because the function returns Ok before reaching it.
## Mandated refactor
Don't short-circuit. Treat SCP form as an implicit `ssh://` URL: normalize it (rewrite `user@host:path` to `ssh://user@host/path`) and continue through the standard scheme + host + userinfo checks. Reject SCP URLs whose username is anything other than `git` (or an explicit policy-configured set). Add host-allowlist scaffolding so a managed policy can pin acceptable git hosts.
## Filed from QA review dispatch
